## Key Organization Patterns

### **Directory Structure**
1. **`src/app/`** - Next.js App Router with route-based organization
2. **`src/core/`** - Core application logic (auth, database, email, etc.)
3. **`src/features/`** - Feature-specific business logic
4. **`src/shared/`** - Shared utilities, components, and types
5. **`src/components/`** - Reusable React components
6. **`src/styles/`** - Global styles and theme configuration

### **Route Organization**
- **`(marketing)/`** - Public marketing pages (blog, docs, contact, etc.)
- **`auth/`** - Authentication flows (sign-in, sign-up, password reset)
- **`admin/`** - Administrative dashboard and account management
- **`home/(user)/`** - Personal user dashboard
- **`home/[account]/`** - Team account management (dynamic routes)

### **Component Patterns**
- **`_components/`** - Route-specific components
- **`src/components/ui/`** - Reusable UI components (shadcn/ui)
- **`src/components/makerkit/`** - Makerkit-specific shared components

### **Data Layer**
- **`src/core/database/`** - Database schemas, clients, and types
- **`src/features/*/server/`** - Server-side business logic and API
- **`src/shared/policies/`** - Authorization and access control policies

### **Configuration**
- **`src/core/config/`** - Application configuration
- **`.env.local`** - Environment-specific variables
- **`supabase/`** - Database migrations and configuration
